The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as semantic and instance segmentation, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep neural networks for joint learning and prediction also suggests that the paper may fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of heuristics and optimization techniques, which could place it under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The application of the proposed method to street scene datasets suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of image datasets and the evaluation of performance metrics could place the paper under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
